Vehicle construction, conveyor technology, aerospace technology. Fish fins behave unexpectedly under lateral pressure: if, for example, you press the finger slightly against the tail fin of a trout, it does not pinch away as expected in the direction of pressure, but rather the fin moves towards the finger against the direction of pressure. This effect is called the Fin Ray Effect. The patented fin jet effect is based on the structure of the individual fin beams. These consist of two fixed struts each, which converge at the top and are firmly attached there. The two struts form a sharp-angled triangle. Between the two bend-elastic flanks there are cross struts, which keep the flanks at a distance and enable elastic movements. This function reversal with lateral force action is the basis of many high-tech solutions.
